message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.NEURON - The paper deals with automated quality control in image segmentation, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of machine learning techniques to predict segmentation quality falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The application of this method to a large-scale medical imaging study makes it relevant to the medical imaging (cs.MED) sub-category. The use of predictive models also falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the use of machine learning techniques to analyze medical images is a common application in the field of neuroscience (cs.NEURON).
